      • toUne

        public static java.lang.Object toUne​(java.lang.String text)
        Returns the proper Java data value based on received String.
        Note: null is not accepted as parameter value.

        Returns:

        • If is Une keyword -> returns its String
        • If is boolean -> returns its Boolean
        • If is number -> returns its Number
        • If is string -> returns its String
        • If is extended type -> returns its instance
        • If is JSON string -> returns its value (if valid)
        • If none of above -> returns its String
        Parameters:
        text -
        Returns:
        The proper data value based on passed string.

      • toUneBasics

        public static java.lang.Object toUneBasics​(java.lang.String text)
        Returns the proper Java data value based on passed String (which has to be any of Une basic types: Boolean, Number, String).
        Note: null is not accepted as parameter value.

        Returns:

        • If is boolean -> returns its Boolean
        • If is number -> returns its Number
        • If is string -> returns its String
        • If none of above -> returns its String
        Parameters:
        text -
        Returns:
        The proper Java data value based on passed String (which has to be any of Une basic types: Boolean, Number, String).
